---

## Required Model File Names

The backend expects the model files to have these exact names:

```text
waterlogging_risk.pkl
drought_risk.pkl
frost_risk.pkl
erosion_risk.pkl
crop_recommender.pkl
crop_labels.pkl
```

If files are named like:

```text
drought_risk(1).pkl
crop_recommender (1)(1).pkl
```

rename them properly before running the backend.

---

## Installation and Setup

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/agri-risk-backend.git
```

### 2. Enter Project Folder

```bash
cd agri-risk-backend/backend
```

### 3. Create Virtual Environment

```bash
python -m venv venv
```

### 4. Activate Virtual Environment

For Windows PowerShell:

```bash
venv\Scripts\activate
```

### 5. Install Requirements

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 6. Run Flask Backend

```bash
python app.py
```

The server will start at:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:5000
```

---

## API Endpoints

### Home Route

```http
GET /
```

Response:

```text
Agri-Risk AI Fusion API is Online. Send GET requests to /predict?lat=...&lon=...
```

---

### Prediction Route

```http
GET /predict?lat=12.9716&lon=77.5946
```

Example:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:5000/predict?lat=12.9716&lon=77.5946
```

